# **PSYCHIC POWERS**

![][image16]

**PSYKERS** are units able to use psychic powers, which can provide a range of battlefield abilities.  Psychic powers can be invoked in different phases, depending on the type and/or description of how the ability is used.

## **USING PSYCHIC POWERS**

### Mastery Level & Choosing Powers

* **MASTERY LEVEL:** Each psyker model has a **MASTERY LEVEL**, which is listed at the end of their ***Psyker*** special rule and determines the number of powers they may select.    
  * **Mastery Level 3 or more**: A model with Mastery Level 3 or higher may roll a die when suffering Perils of the Warp.  If the result is a 5+, they ignore all effects of Perils of the Warp.   
* **AVAILABLE POWERS:** The powers available to a psyker will be determined based on the unit’s codex entry.  
  * Unless otherwise specified in their Codex Entry, a psyker knows 1 power for each Mastery Level they have.  A ML1 psyker knows 1 power, an ML2 psyker knows 2 powers, etc.  
  * If the psyker model’s codex book contains a list of specific powers that are available to that army's psykers, powers must be selected from that codex unless otherwise specified.   
  * If a psyker’s codex entry indicates specific powers available to that psyker, those are the powers that must be used.  
  * If the psyker’s codex entry says the unit may draw powers from specific psychic disciplines, powers may be selected from among those allowed disciplines.   
* **SELECTING POWERS:** Players are always free to choose whatever powers they would like from the available list.  
* **BROTHERHOOD OF PSYKERS:** A Brotherhood of Psykers is a special type of psyker where multiple models in the unit are collectively treated as a single psyker for purposes of mastery level and available powers.    
  * The unit takes psychic tests (see below) using the highest leadership within the unit (an attached Independent Character’s leadership is never used for the psychic test).  
  * If the unit suffers from perils of the warp (see below), the unit’s owner chooses a model in the unit to suffer the effects.

### Invoking Psychic Powers

* **WHEN TO USE POWERS:** The description for a specific psychic power will indicate the type of power (which determines when it can be invoked) and/or the description will specify exactly when it can be invoked. In addition, the following applies to using powers:  
  * **RESERVES:** Psykers that are not deployed on the table but that are eligible to enter from reserves may invoke psychic powers immediately after arriving from reserve and before the normal part of the movement phase.  
  * **REACTIONS:**  Psychic powers may NOT be invoked when performing a reaction, such as Return Fire or Stand & Shoot.  
* **NUMBER OF POWERS**: Each Psyker can invoke a number of powers per turn depending on its mastery level.  
  * **Mastery Level 1**: Invoke one power per player turn  
  * **Mastery Level 2 or more**: Invoke two powers per player turn    
  * Under no circumstances may a psyker invoke more than two powers per player turn.  
* **WARP LIMIT:** Each player may not successfully invoke the same power more than once in a single turn, even if the power is known by multiple different psyker units.  
* **DISTURBANCE IN THE WARP**: As more psychic powers are invoked in a player turn, it becomes harder for other psykers to channel the warp.  For every two psychic powers successfully invoked in a player turn, subsequent psychic tests suffer a \-1 to their Ld test. These are cumulative (e.g. invoking a 5th power would incur a \-2 Ld).  
* **FORCE WEAPONS:** Taking a psychic test to utilize a **Force Weapon** does NOT count as using a power  
* **TARGETING POWERS:** Unless otherwise stated, psychic powers require line of sight to the target.  
  * **TRANSPORTS:** Psykers embarked on a transport may use powers that target themselves and/or friendly units on the units they are embarked with. Psykers may use psychic powers to target units (friendly or enemy) that are outside of their transport so long as a **FIRE PORT** is available and it has line of sight to the target location.

