### Deny the Witch

Opposing psykers may have an opportunity to prevent a psychic power from being invoked by **DENYING THE WITCH**.  

* **WHEN TO DENY THE WITCH:** A deny the witch attempt may only be attempted in the following circumstances:  
  * The psychic power is targeting an opposing unit containing an opposing psyker.  
  * The psychic power is targeting any unit (friendly or opposing) that is within 6” of an opposing psyker.  
  * An opposing psyker is within 6” of the psyker attempting to invoke the power.  
  * Each invoked psychic power may only have one attempt to deny the witch made against it.  
* **ROLLING TO DENY THE WITCH:** After the psychic test is passed, both players roll a D6 and add the mastery level of their respective psyker (i.e. the psyker invoking the power and the psyker attempting to deny the witch).  
  * **If the opposing player’s total is HIGHER** then the deny the witch attempt is successful and the power is nullified.  
  * **If the opposing player’s total is EQUAL or LOWER** then the deny the witch attempt fails and the psychic power goes off successfully.  
* **PSYCHIC HOODS**: Psychic hood or similar wargear/abilities may extend the range of where a psyker can attempt to deny the witch and/or provide modifiers to Deny the Witch.  Psychic Hoods (and equivalent wargear) extend the range of where a psyker may attempt to deny the witch to 24”.

## **POWER TYPES**

There are a number of different types of psychic power, which have distinct names in the 6th and 7th edition rulebooks and codexes.  3rd-5th edition codexes do not specifically reference these types, but the power description itself will instead describe when and how the power is invoked and resolved.

* **BLESSINGS:** Blessings are powers which target a friendly unit and confer some benefit.  
  * Invoked any time during the psyker’s **MOVEMENT PHASE** unless otherwise noted.  
  * **Duration:** Lasts until the start of the psyker’s own next turn.  
  * Blessings with the same effects can stack cumulatively if the power was a differently named power. Exact copies of a specific blessing (i.e. same name) cannot be stacked on the same unit.  
  * Characteristics cannot be modified above a 10 or below a 1\.  
  * If a psyker with an active blessing is removed from play, their blessings are immediately canceled.  
* **CONJURATION:** These are powers that can summon outside forces onto the battlefield.  
  * Invoked at the start of the psykers **MOVEMENT PHASE** unless otherwise noted.  
    * Unit using a conjuration power may not perform any other actions the turn this power is used (no movement, shooting, other psychic powers, charging, etc.)  
    * Any doubles that are rolled during the psychic test automatically inflicts perils of the warp, regardless of whether the conjuration was successful or not.  
    * Can only summon daemons that match the psykers chaos mark.  
    * Each Psyker may only *successfully* cast a selected conjuration power once per game.  
    * Summoned units that are also psykers may not select conjuration powers.  
  * Units that are summoned arrive following the same rules as for **DEEP STRIKING** units.  The **CENTER MODEL** for the deep strike must be placed within the specified range of conjuration power.  
* **MALEDICTION**: These powers weaken and hinder opposing units.   
  * Invoked during the psykers **MOVEMENT PHASE** unless otherwise noted.  
  * **Duration:** Last until the start of the psyker’s own next turn.  
  * Maledictions with the same effects can stack cumulatively if the power was a differently named power. Exact copies of a specific malediction (i.e. same name) cannot be stacked on the same unit.  
  * Characteristics cannot be modified above a 10 or below a 1\.  
  * If a psyker with an active malediction is removed from play, their maledictions are immediately canceled.  
* **WITCHFIRE**: These powers take the form of a **RANGED ATTACK** and count as a shooting attack.  Psychic powers which say they count as a shooting attack (but don’t explicitly state they are witchfire) are still counted as a witchfire power and are subject to the rules below.  
  * Invoked during the psyker’s **SHOOTING PHASE.**  
  * Count as a shooting attack for the model. Thus the model may not make any additional ranged attacks unless normally allowed to make more than one ranged attack.   
  * Witchfire attacks are treated as **ASSAULT** weapons unless otherwise specified.  
  * **ROLLING TO HIT**: After successfully invoking the power, the psyker must still roll to hit as with a normal shooting attack. As with any ranged attack, the psyker must have line of sight to the target and be within the specified range.  
  * **NO PROFILE:** If the witchfire ability does NOT have a weapon/attack profile, then the psyker does NOT need to roll to hit unless otherwise specified.  
  * A psyker may only invoke one witchfire ability per turn, unless the model is allowed to shoot more than one weapon AND the psyker knows two or more different witchfire abilities.  
* **WITCHFIRE \- BEAMS:** Beams are a witchfire power (above) with the following additional rules:  
  * Draw a line between the psyker and a chosen point within the power’s range.  
  * The power may or may not require line of sight to the chosen point.  
  * Each unit with a model in the path of the beam takes a number of hits equal to the number of models in that unit that are under the path. Unsaved wounds from the beam attack may be given to any models in the unit that have the same saving throw (as per resolving normal shooting attacks).  
* **WITCHFIRE \- FOCUSED:** Focused powers are witchfire powers that allow the psyker to attack a specific model a a target unit, and are subject to the following additional rules:  
  * When making the psychic test to invoke the power, if the die roll was equal to or within two points below the psyker's leadership, then the opposing player may choose which model in the target unit is affected, otherwise the psyker’s owner chooses which model is affected.  
* **WITCHFIRE \- MAELSTROM:** Witchfire power that automatically hits all units (whether friendly or enemy) within the affected are (typically a maximum range centered on the psyker).   
  * Line of sight, being engaged or not in melee, intervening terrain, etc. are ignored unless otherwise specified.  
  * May include effects that are blessings or maledictions as well.  
* **WITCHFIRE \- NOVA:** Nova witchfire attacks automatically targets and hits all ENEMY units within the powers maximum range.  
  * Line of sight, being engaged or not in melee, intervening terrain, etc. are ignored unless otherwise specified.

